		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Find the centre of mass of a lamina bounded by \(y^2 = {@aa@}x\), for \(0\leq x \leq {@ub@}\).</p>
<p><br></p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li> \(\bar{x} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</li>
  <li> \(\bar{y} =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[We can follow the approach above, noting that the region is bounded by \(x=0\), \(x={@ub@}\), \(y=\sqrt{{@aa@}x}\) and&nbsp;\(y=-\sqrt{{@aa@}x}\).Hence&nbsp;<br><br>\[ \bar{x} = \frac{\int_0^{@ub@} 2x \sqrt{{@aa@}x}&nbsp;&nbsp;\mathrm{d}x}{\int_0^{@ub@}
2\sqrt{{@aa@}x} \mathrm{d}x} = \frac{&nbsp; {@integrate(2*x*sqrt(aa*x),x,0,ub)@}&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;}{&nbsp; &nbsp;{@integrate(2*sqrt(aa*x),x,0,ub)@}} ={@xbar@}. \]<br><br>Then either by symmetry or the formula we can see that \(\bar{y}=0\).<br><br>Alternatively
we can work with respect to \(y\). First we compute the total mass of the lamina taking vertical strips. Rearranging the equation gives \(y_{max} = \sqrt{{@aa@}\times{@ub@}}= {@ymax@}\), \(y_{min} = -{@ymax@}\). The total mass is then given by: <br>\[
mass = \rho \int_{-{@ymax@}}^{{@ymax@}} ({@ub@} - \frac{y^2}{{@aa@}})dy = 2\rho\times{@ub@}\times{@ymax@} - \frac{2\rho}{3\times{@aa@}}\times\frac{{@ymax@}^3}{{@aa@}} = {@tma@}\rho\]
<br><br>Similarly we compute the total moment to be:<br>\[ \begin{align*} moment &amp;= \rho\int_{-{@ymax@}}^{{@ymax@}} x({@ub@} - \frac{y^2}{{@aa@}})dy\\ &amp;= \rho\int_{-{@ymax@}}^{{@ymax@}}&nbsp; \left(\frac{y^2}{{@2*aa@}}+\frac{{@ub@}}{2}\right)&nbsp;
\left({@ub@} - \frac{y^2}{{@aa@}}\right)dy\\ &amp;=&nbsp; {@integrate((y^2/(2*aa)+ub/2)*(ub-y^2/aa),y,-ymax,ymax)@}\rho \end{align*} \]
<br><br>Taking the ratio gives<br>\[\bar{x}= {@ratsimp(integrate((y^2/(2*aa)+ub/2)*(ub-y^2/aa),y,-ymax,ymax)/integrate((ub-y^2/aa),y,-ymax,ymax))@} \]<span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;"><br>By symmetry, \(\bar{y} = 0\).</span><br>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
